Line 3. Add the amounts in column (c) of line 2. Do not enter more than $3,000 for one qualifying person or $6,000 for two or more persons. If you completed Part 3, enter the amount from line 31. Dollars.
Line 4. Enter your earned income. See instructions. Dollars.
Line 5. If married filing jointly, enter your spouse's earned income (if your spouse was a student or was disabled, see the instructions); all others, enter the amount from line 4. Dollars.
Line 6. Enter the smallest of line 3, 4, or 5. Dollars.
Line 7. Enter the amount from Form 1040, line 38, Form 1040 A, line 22, or Form 1040 N R, line 37. Dollars.
Line 8. Enter on line 8 the decimal amount shown below that applies to the amount on line 7.
Line 9. Multiply line 6 by the decimal amount on line 8. If you paid 2012 expenses in 2013, see the instructions. Dollars.
Line 10. Tax liability limit. Enter the amount from the Credit Limit Worksheet in the instructions. Dollars.
Line 11. Credit for child and dependent care expenses. Enter the smaller of line 9 or line 10 here and on Form 1040, line 48, Form 1040 A, line 29, or Form 1040 N R, line 46. Dollars.

Page 2. Part 3. Dependent Care Benefits. Line 12. Enter the total amount of dependent care benefits you received in 2013. Amounts you received as an employee should be shown in box 10 of your Form(s) W-2. Do not include amounts reported as wages in box 1 of Form(s) W-2. If you were self-employed or a partner, include amounts you received under a dependent care assistance program from your sole proprietorship or partnership. Dollars.
Line 13. Enter the amount, if any, you carried over from 2012 and used in 2013 during the grace period. See instructions. Dollars.
Line 14. Enter the amount, if any, you forfeited or carried forward to 2014. See instructions. Open parenthesis. Dollars.
Line 15. Combine lines 12 through 14. See instructions. Dollars.
Line 16. Enter the total amount of qualified expenses incurred in 2013 for the care of the qualifying person(s). Dollars.
Line 17. Enter the smaller of line 15 or 16. Dollars.
Line 18. Enter your earned income. See instructions. Dollars.

Line 19. Enter the amount shown below that applies to you. If married filing jointly, enter your spouse's earned income (if your spouse was a student or was disabled, see the instructions for line 5). If married filing separately, see instructions. All others, enter the amount from line 18. Dollars.
Line 20. Enter the smallest of line 17, 18, or 19. Dollars.
Line 21. Enter $5,000 ($2,500 if married filing separately and you were required to enter your spouse’s earned income on line 19). Dollars.
Line 23. Subtract line 22 from line 15. Dollars.
Line 24. Deductible benefits. Enter the smallest of line 20, 21, or 22. Also, include this amount on the appropriate line(s) of your return. See instructions. Dollars.

Line 25. Excluded benefits. Form 1040 and 1040 N R filers: If you checked "No" on line 22, enter the smaller of line 20 or 21. Otherwise, subtract line 24 from the smaller of line 20 or line 21. If zero or less, enter zero. Form 1040 A filers: Enter the smaller of line 20 or line 21. Dollars.

Line 26. Taxable benefits. Form 1040 and 1040N R filers: Subtract line 25 from line 23. If zero or  less, enter zero. Also, include this amount on Form 1040, line 7, or Form 1040 N R, line 8. On the dotted line next to Form 1040, line 7, or Form 1040 N R, line 8, enter "D C B." Form 1040 A filers: Subtract line 25 from line 15. Also, include this amount on Form 1040 A,  line 7. In the space to the left of line 7, enter “D C B”. Dollars.
Part 3. Dependent Care Benefits. To claim the child and dependent care credit, complete lines 27 through 31 below. Line 27. Enter $3,000 ($6,000 if two or more qualifying persons). Dollars.
Line 28. Form 1040 and 1040N R filers: Add lines 24 and 25. Form 1040A filers: Enter the amount from line 25	. Dollars.
Line 29. Subtract line 28 from line 27. If zero or less, stop. You cannot take the credit. Exception. If you paid 2012 expenses in 2013, see the instructions for line 9. Dollars.
Line 30. Complete line 2 on the front of this form. Do not include in column (c) any benefits shown  on line 28 above. Then, add the amounts in column (c) and enter the total here. Dollars.
Line 31. Enter the smaller of line 29 or 30. Also, enter this amount on line 3 on the front of this form and complete lines 4 through 11. Dollars.
